Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 Jan (MENA)--Egypt has welcomed the Israeli 
and PLO decision to resume negotiations on implementing the 
Gaza-Jericho accord next week. 
  In a statement made today, Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa 
expressed his hope that the two sides will reach an agreement to 
implement the Declaration of Principles signed between them in 
letter and spirit. 
  He emphasized the need to realize the goals of the 
declaration: Israel's withdrawal from Gaza and Jericho according 
to the agreement, establishing Palestinian authority, and an 
agreement on the security measures stipulated in the 
declaration. He also affirmed the need to pave the way for 
future steps toward establishing self-rule in all the 
Palestinian territories occupied since 1967 and prepare for the 
final negotiations in two years. 

